          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was 6-mg/cm**2 natural iron.The Fe-54",
                "component of natural iron cannot produced neutrons",
                "with energies above those of the IAS group.The Fe-57",
                "and Fe-58 components can. Spectra taken with an Fe-57",
                "target indicated no sharp levels near the Co-56 AAS.",
                "The 0.33% Fe-58 component cannot produced a detectable",
                "neutron group except possibly for its IAS transition",
                "which would lie beside the Fe-56 IAS group."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".Two 2.54-cm*20-cm Ne-224 liquid scintillation",
                "detectors were placed side by side in a earthen-",
                "shielded bunker for these longer-flight-path",
                "measurements.The 9-m measurements utilized three",
                "similar detectors in concrete shields arranged so that",
                "data for three angles were obtained simultaneously."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USACLU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ".The measurements were made with the",
                "University of Colorado rotating-beam neutron time-of-",
                "flight spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " New system employs neutron detectors at fixed,",
                "well-shielded positions and varies the angle of",
                "incidence of the beam upon the target to obtained an",
                "angular distribution.Initial data were obtained at 9 m",
                "flight path where Gaussian unfolding procedures were",
                "necessary to extract the area of the AAS peak at",
                " 1.45 MeV from that of the neighboring 1.72 MeV level."
              ]
            }
          ],
